{[%evp 0,25,22,-21,34,34,34,34,34,34,59,60,68,59,49,49,63,56,40,47,39,28,25,41,
48,37,18,28]} 1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bf5 (4... Bg4 5. cxd5 Bxf3 6.
Qxf3 cxd5 7. Bb5+ Nc6 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. b3 e6 10. O-O {1-0 (42) Roiz,M (2652)
-Holzke,F (2526) Rijeka 2010 CBM 136 [Roiz,M]}) (4... a6 {This move is
perfectly playable, but you can be ready to meet} 5. d4 (5. h3 {is a nice try
to avoid long theory})) (4... g6 {entering the "Schlechter Slav" is possible,
but I think that those positions are quite passive} 5. d4 Bg7 6. Be2 O-O 7. O-O
) (4... e6 $1 {I reccomend this move which has the obvious drawback that White
can always play d4 and enter Meran. On the other hand, this is not that
dangerous and If White stays in the 1.c4 territory Black has a good game.}) 5.
cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 Bc8 {If you need to play such move then something is wrong.
The position remains pretty solid for Black, but I couldn't reccomend such
setup.} (6... Qb6 7. Nxd5 Nxd5 8. Qxd5 e6 9. Qb5+ {1-0 (76) Mekhitarian,K  
(2554)-Dordzhieva,D (2334) Chess.com INT 2021}) (6... Qd7 7. Ne5 $16) 7. d4 e6
8. Bd3 Nc6 9. O-O Be7 10. Bd2 O-O 11. Rac1 Bd7 12. Ne5 Nxe5 13. dxe5 {1-0 (32)
So,W (2767)-Mamedyarov,S (2767) Chess.com INT 2019} *

