{Model game for White.} 1. Nf3 {In this game I will show you, what we should
avoid} d5 2. c4 c6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. Qc2 Nbd7 6. b3 Bd6 7. Bb2 O-O 8. h3 {
we have a very similar position to our mainline. The big difference is that
Black's knight is on d7 instead of b8. This small difference changes a lot.} e5
(8... a6 {is a good waiting move}) 9. cxd5 cxd5 $2 {this is just a mistake} (
9... Nxd5 $1 {[%cal Rd8e7] is quite a playable line where Black can fight for
the equality}) 10. Nb5 Bb8 11. Rc1 e4 (11... a6 $1 {Black's best chance was}
12. Nc7 Ra7 $1 {White needs to find} 13. Ng5 $1 b5 (13... h6 $4 14. Nge6 $1 $18
) 14. Nxd5 Bb7 15. Nxf6+ Nxf6 {White is a pawn up, but the position is far
from clear}) 12. Nfd4 a6 13. Nc7 Bxc7 14. Qxc7 Qxc7 15. Rxc7 $18 {This is
White's dream position. The endgame is completely lost. White has c-file and
bishop pair.} Ne5 16. Be2 Rb8 17. O-O Bd7 18. Rfc1 Rfd8 (18... Rfc8 19. Rxc8+
Rxc8 20. Rxc8+ Bxc8 21. Nb5 axb5 22. Bxe5 $18) 19. g4 Ng6 20. Kh2 Ne8 21. R7c5
Be6 22. Kg3 Ne7 23. Nxe6 fxe6 24. d3 exd3 25. Bxd3 Rbc8 26. f4 (26. Rxc8 Rxc8
27. Rxc8 Nxc8 28. Kf4 $18) 26... Rxc5 27. Rxc5 g6 28. e4 $6 Kf7 (28... dxe4 {
Black missed a very good opportunity} 29. Bxe4 Rd2 $132) 29. Kf3 Rd7 30. Ke3
Nd6 31. e5 Ndc8 32. Rc1 Na7 33. Ba3 Nac6 34. Bd6 Na7 35. a4 Nac8 36. Bc5 Rc7
37. a5 Ke8 38. Kd2 Nc6 39. b4 Rf7 40. b5 $6 (40. Ra1 $16) (40. Ke3) 40... Nxa5
41. Rb1 axb5 42. f5 gxf5 43. gxf5 Nc4+ 44. Bxc4 bxc4 45. fxe6 Rc7 46. Bb4 Rc6
47. Kc3 Rxe6 48. Kd4 Nb6 49. Bd6 Nc8 50. Kxd5 Rh6 51. Rxb7 Rxh3 52. Bb4 $4 (52.
Rb8 $1 Kd8 53. Kc6 $18 {[%cal Rc6b7,Rd6c7,Re5e6]}) 52... c3 53. Rc7 Nb6+ 54.
Kc6 Rh6+ 55. Bd6 Nc4 56. Kd5 Nxd6 57. exd6 Rh3 58. Rc4 Kd7 59. Rc7+ Kd8 60. Rc4
Kd7 61. Rc7+ Kd8 62. Rc4 Kd7 63. Rc7+ Kd8 64. Rc4 1/2-1/2

