1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. b3 Bd6 6. Bb2 O-O 7. Be2 (7. h3 {
is a trendy new move, tried many times by the German prodigy Vincent Keymer.}
Nbd7 {was tried by Pavel Eljanov. He didn't have any problems after} (7... Re8
8. Qc2 (8. d4 {White should probably already transpose to the Meran}) 8... e5
9. cxd5 cxd5 10. Nb5 Nc6 11. Nxd6 Qxd6 12. Bb5 Bd7 13. O-O (13. Bxc6 $1 Bxc6
14. O-O Rac8 $11) 13... Nb4 {0-1 (13) Keymer,V (2558)-Grischuk,A (2777) Chess.
com INT 2020}) 8. Qc2 e5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 $1 10. Be2 Qe7 11. Ne4 Ba3 (11... Bc7 $5
{[%cal Rf7f5]}) 12. Bxa3 Qxa3 13. O-O Qe7 14. Ng3 N7f6 15. Rac1 Re8 {1/2-1/2  
(15) Chigaev,M (2630)-Eljanov,P (2671) Biel 2021} 16. d3 $5 {I think White's
position is more flexible and he can try to push for an advantage here.}) (7.
Qc2 e5 8. cxd5 cxd5 9. Nb5 Nc6 10. Nxd6 Qxd6 {Is the main line and will be
discussed in the next games}) 7... e5 8. cxd5 cxd5 9. Nb5 Nc6 10. Nxd6 Qxd6 11.
O-O (11. d4 {is possible, but I think Black has no problems after:} e4 12. Ne5
Nd7 13. Nxc6 bxc6 $11 {[%cal Ra7a5,Rf7f5,Rf5f4] 0-1 (26) Bocharov,D (2517)
-Kobalia,M (2600) Sochi 2021}) 11... d4 $1 {Using the fact that White didn't
play d4} 12. exd4 e4 $1 13. Ne5 Nxd4 14. Nc4 Qd8 $11 15. Rc1 Re8 16. Ne3 Be6
17. Bc4 Bxc4 18. Rxc4 Nc6 19. Qa1 Re6 20. Rd1 Qd3 21. Rc3 Qd7 22. d3 Rd6 23.
Rc5 $6 exd3 $1 $15 24. Bxf6 gxf6 25. h3 Re8 $2 (25... b6 $1 26. Rc4 Ne5 $17)
26. Nf5 $11 Rde6 27. Qc3 Rd8 28. Rc4 Kh8 29. Rg4 Ne5 $4 30. Rd4 Qe8 31. f4 $4 (
31. Rxd8 Qxd8 32. f4 $18) 31... Rc8 $1 $19 32. Qa1 Nf3+ 33. gxf3 Re2 34. Nh4
Qg8+ 35. Kh1 Rcc2 {0-1 (35) Ponkratov,P (2659)-Motylev,A (2624) Ufa 2021} *

