1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. b3 Bd6 6. Bb2 O-O 7. Qc2 {I think
after this move, Black has an excellent play. And despite that this is the
mainline, my opinion is that it doesn't promise any advantage for White. A
general rule in such positions is that Qc2 is good after Nbd7.} e5 8. cxd5 cxd5
9. Nb5 Nc6 10. Nxd6 Qxd6 {White is not developed, he has bishop pair, but
Black's centre and activity fully compensate for it. There are four critical
continuations in this position.} 11. d4 (11. Bb5 {Probably the most
straightforward one. White is attacking the e5-pawn.} Nb4 $1 12. Qc1 d4 13.
exd4 (13. a3 Bd7 $5 14. Bc4 Nc6 $15 {[%cal Rd7g4,Ra8c8]}) 13... exd4 (13...
Nfd5 $1 14. dxe5 Qg6 15. O-O a6 16. Bc4 Nf4 $17) 14. O-O a6 15. a3 Nbd5 16. Bc4
Bg4 17. Nxd4 Nf4 18. Re1 Rac8 19. Qb1 {Black has more than enough compensation
for the pawn and the game eventually ended in a draw. ½-½ (87) Anton
Guijarro,D (2616)-Ponomariov,R (2715) Madrid 2016}) (11. Rc1 $6 {I believe
that this continuation is just bad, I couldn't find equality for White here}
Bg4 $1 12. Qc5 Qe6 13. Bb5 {this natural move is losing on a spot} Rfc8 $19 {
Black is already winning} 14. Bxc6 Rxc6 15. Qb4 Rxc1+ 16. Bxc1 Rc8 17. O-O Bxf3
18. gxf3 e4 19. Kh1 Qh3 20. Rg1 Qxf3+ {0-1 (20) Benitez Lozano,J (2350)
-Salinas Herrera,P (2514) Chess.com INT 2020}) (11. Be2 {This slow move gives
Black the initiative} Bg4 12. h3 (12. Qd1 Rfe8 13. O-O $11) 12... Bh5 (12...
Bxf3 13. Bxf3 Nb4 14. Qb1 e4 15. Be2 Rac8 16. Bc3 d4 17. exd4 (17. Bxb4 Qxb4
18. a3 Qe7 19. O-O d3 $17) 17... Nbd5) 13. d3 e4 (13... d4 $1 $15) 14. dxe4
dxe4 15. Rd1 Qb4+ 16. Bc3 exf3 17. Bxb4 Nxb4 18. Qc4 fxe2 19. Ra1 a5 20. g4 Bg6
21. a3 Bd3 22. Qf4 Nc2+ 23. Kd2 Rfd8 {0-1 (23) Gabrielian,A (2448)-Shirov,A  
(2662) Lichess.org INT 2021}) 11... Nb4 12. Qb1 (12. Qd1 e4 13. Ne5 Ne8 14. h3
f6 15. Ng4 h5 16. Nh2 f5 17. a3 f4 18. Bc1 (18. axb4 fxe3 19. fxe3 Qg3+ 20. Kd2
Rf2+ 21. Be2 Bd7 {The engine says 0.00. But from a human point of view the
position is just very hard for Black to defend}) 18... Nc6 19. exf4 Nc7 {
0-1 (39) Lie,K (2521)-Shirov,A (2664) Chess.com INT 2020}) 12... Qc7 13. dxe5
Nc2+ 14. Kd1 Bf5 15. exf6 d4 16. exd4 Nxd4 17. Bxd4 Bxb1 18. Rxb1 Rfd8 19. Bd3
Rxd4 20. Nxd4 Qc3 21. Bc4 Qxd4+ 22. Kc2 Qxf2+ 23. Kc3 Qxf6+ 24. Kc2 b5 25. Bxb5
Qf5+ 26. Bd3 Rc8+ 27. Kd2 Rd8 {0-1 (27) Howell,D (2666)-Erigaisi,A (2616) Riga
2021} *

