{For the end, I will try to give you some advice on how to face Meran
Variation. Against 6.Qc2, I quite like the idea of Magnus Carlsen and Daniil
Dubov 6...a5. There are just a few games in the database, but Black is doing
quite well. Of course, you can study the mainline (6...Bd6 as well).} 1. d4 d5
2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c6 4. e3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Nbd7 6. Qc2 a5 {This is a good waiting
move. Black is waiting for a bishop move to continue with dxc4 and b5. On the
other hand, with a bishop on f8, we avoid the dangerous "Shirov Gambit" 6...
Bd6 7.g4} 7. h3 (7. b3 Bb4 8. Bd3 Ne4 9. Bxe4 dxe4 10. Nd2 f5 $11 {0-1 (38)
Nesterov,A (2517) -Paravyan,D (2653) Chess.com INT 2020}) (7. Bd3 dxc4 8. Bxc4
b5 9. Bd3 b4 $1 (9... Bb7 10. O-O Rc8 11. e4 b4 12. Na4 c5 13. d5 exd5 14. exd5
Bxd5 15. Re1+ $14 {0-1 (34) Rychagov,A (2545)-Deac,B (2625) Lichess.org INT
2020}) 10. Ne4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 Bb7 12. O-O Rc8 (12... Be7 $11 {[%cal Rh7h6,Ra8c8]
} 13. Bxh7 c5 $40 14. Be4 Qb6 $132) 13. Ne5 $2 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Qc7 $15 {0-1 (42)
Krishnater,K (2410)-Stany,G (2522) Chess.com INT 2020}) (7. a3) (7. a4 Bd6 8.
Be2 O-O 9. O-O dxc4 10. Bxc4 e5 11. Ba2 Qe7 12. h3 Bb4 $1 13. dxe5 Nxe5 14. Nd4
c5 15. Ndb5 Be6 16. Bxe6 fxe6 17. e4 Nh5 18. Ne2 g5 19. Be3 g4 20. Ng3 Qh4 $19
{1-0 (44) Yu,Y (2709)-Carlsen,M (2863) chess24.com INT 2020}) 7... Be7 8. g4
