{I will try to offer you a very simple repertoire against Meran too. It is
very easy to remember and without any theoretical problems. Of course, the
main lines are more reliable, but required serious knowledge.} 1. c4 c6 2. Nf3
d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. d4 Nbd7 6. Bd3 Bd6 7. O-O (7. e4 dxe4 8. Nxe4 Nxe4 9.
Bxe4 e5 {we should hurry with this move} 10. O-O exd4 11. Bg5 (11. Qxd4 Qf6 12.
Rd1 Be7 13. Be3 Qxd4 14. Nxd4 $14 {White is slightly more active. But the
position is symmetrical and quite drawish ½-½ (61) Bareev,E (2702)-Anand,V  
(2762) Dortmund 2000 CBM 078 [Lutz,C]}) 11... Nf6 12. Qxd4 h6 13. Bh4 Be7 14.
Qe5 Be6 $2 (14... Qd6 $1 15. Qxd6 Bxd6 16. Bxf6 gxf6 $11 {the bishop pair
compensate the ruined structure.}) 15. Bc2 O-O 16. Rad1 $14 {0-1 (73) Gelfand,
B (2737)-Ivanchuk,V (2751) Nice 2008}) 7... O-O (7... b6) 8. e4 (8. Qc2 e5 9.
cxd5 cxd5 10. e4 exd4 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 12. exd5 h6 13. Nxd4 Qh4 14. Nf3 Qh5 15.
Bh7+ Kh8 16. Qf5 Qxf5 17. Bxf5 Nf6 18. Bxc8 Rfxc8 $11 {1/2-1/2 (58) Duda,J  
(2743)-Harikrishna,P (2732) Wijk aan Zee 2021} 19. Rd1 Rd8 20. Be3 Be7) (8. b3
{doesn't work very well here} e5 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. Nb5 Bb8 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Bb2
Nxf3+ 13. Qxf3 $4 (13. gxf3 Bh3 {with an attack}) 13... Bg4 14. Bxf6 Qd7 15.
Bf5 Bxf5 {[%cal Rf5g4,Rd7b5]} 16. Rfd1 Bg4 17. Rxd5 Bxf3 18. Rxd7 Bc6 {0-1 (18)
Mikhalevski,V (2535)-Motylev,A (2653) Minsk 2015}) 8... dxc4 9. Bxc4 e5 10. Be3
(10. Bg5 Qe7 (10... exd4 11. Qxd4 Qe7 $11) 11. Re1 Rd8 12. d5 h6 13. Bh4 Nf8
14. dxc6 bxc6 15. Qc2 Bg4 $15 {[%csl Rc3][%cal Rf8g6,Rd6c5] 1/2-1/2 (42)
Artemiev,V (2704)-Murzin,V (2502) Krasnaya Polyana 2021}) 10... exd4 11. Bxd4
Qc7 12. Kh1 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bxe5 Qxe5 15. f4 Qc5 16. Bd3 Rd8 17. Qf3 Be6
18. h3 Rxd3 19. Qxd3 Bc4 20. Qd2 Bxf1 21. Rxf1 Re8 22. Rd1 Qb4 23. a3 Qc4 24.
Qd4 Qxd4 25. Rxd4 Re7 26. e5 Nd7 27. g3 Kf8 28. Kg2 Nc5 29. Kf3 f6 30. Rd8+ Kf7
31. Ne4 Nxe4 32. Kxe4 fxe5 33. fxe5 Re8 34. Rd7+ Re7 35. Rd8 Re8 36. Rd7+ Re7
37. Rd8 {1/2-1/2 (37) Giri,A (2769)-Ding,L (2759) Shenzhen 2017} *

