{[%evp 0,42,16,-18,37,39,44,-5,8,-13,19,5,5,5,5,15,26,15,24,20,11,11,20,5,20,
20,35,35,35,-5,4,-1,-14,-65,-71,-15,-6,-6,-10,-10,-7,5,0,0,0]} 1. c4 c6 2. Nf3
d5 3. g3 Nf6 4. Bg2 Bf5 5. O-O {A flexible move, which could transpose to
other systems. In this line, we will examine the independent plans.} e6 6. cxd5
exd5 $1 (6... cxd5 7. Qb3 $14) 7. d3 (7. Qb3 Qb6 8. d3 Qxb3 9. axb3 Na6 {
transposes to Eljanov-Beliavsky, examined in a sub-line of Line 2.}) 7... Na6
$5 {The most restrictive move order.} (7... Be7 8. Qb3 Qb6 9. Qc2 O-O 10. Nc3 {
[%csl Gb6] leaves the black queen a bit exposed.}) 8. Nc3 (8. Qb3 $2 Nc5 $1)
8... Be7 {Black is very solid and White's main plan is preparing e2-e4.} 9. Nd4
(9. a3 O-O 10. Qc2 h6 (10... d4 11. Ne4 c5 $13) 11. e4 Bh7 12. Rd1 Nc5 13. Nd4
a5 $11 14. b3 Re8 15. Rb1 Bf8 16. f3 Rc8 $15 {Laiz Ibanez,H (2269)-Repka,C  
(2454) Almazan 2017 (0-1, 36)}) 9... Bg6 10. e4 O-O $1 {Only by maintaining
the tension can Black reach the equality. The pawn on d3 is likely to become a
target and it also interrupts the communication between the white queen and
the knight on d4.} 11. e5 {The critical line.} (11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Nxd5 cxd5 13.
Ne2 {Moussard,J (2567)-Tregubov,P (2589) Bastia 2017 (½-½, 55)} Bh5 $11) (11.
Nde2 dxe4 12. dxe4 Nc5 13. Qc2 Qd3 14. Qxd3 Nxd3 15. Nf4 Nxc1 $11 16. Raxc1
Rfd8 (16... Rad8 17. Rfd1 Bb4 18. Nxg6 hxg6 19. Kf1 g5 $11 {Salov,V (2550)
-Chandler,M (2595) Leningrad 1987 (½-½, 47)}) 17. Rfd1 Kf8 18. h3 Rxd1+ 19.
Rxd1 Rd8 20. Rxd8+ Bxd8 21. Kf1 {½-½ Sturua,Z (2548)-Duda,J (2666) Gjakova
2016}) 11... Nd7 12. f4 {White seems to have achieved a lot. The immediate
threat is f4-f5, winning the bishop or (after ...h7-h6), burying it alive.
Black can use his better development to fight against this plan.} (12. e6 $2
Ndc5 13. exf7+ Rxf7 14. Bh3 Bxd3 (14... Nxd3 15. Be6 Bf6 16. Bxf7+ Kxf7 $19)
15. Ne6 {Garcia Garcia,A (2247)-Omariev,M (2304) Chess.com INT 2021 (1-0, 23)}
Qb6 $19) 12... Bc5 (12... Nb4 {is interesting but probably not entirely sound.}
13. f5 Bc5 14. Be3 Qc7 15. Qd2 (15. fxg6 Qxe5 $11 16. gxf7+ Rxf7 17. Rxf7 Qxe3+
18. Kh1 Kxf7 19. Nf5 Qg5 20. Qb3 Nxd3 21. Ne4 Nf2+ 22. Nxf2 Qxf5 23. Nd3 Kg8
24. Qxb7 Rd8 25. Nxc5 Nxc5 26. Qxc6 Ne4) 15... Qxe5 16. Rf4 Rae8 17. Bf2 (17.
Re1 Bxd4 18. Rxd4 c5 19. Rf4 Bxf5 20. Bf2 Qf6 21. g4 Qh6 22. gxf5 Nxd3 $11)
17... Bh5 18. Rh4 a5 19. a3 Na6 20. h3 h6 21. Re1 (21. Nb3 Bxf2+ 22. Qxf2 Nf6
$13) 21... Qf6 22. Rf1 g5 23. Rxh5 Bxd4 24. h4 gxh4 25. Rxh6 hxg3 $5 26. Rxf6
gxf2+ 27. Kh1 Nxf6 28. Qg5+ Kh8 29. Bf3 $40) 13. Be3 (13. Nce2 Nb4 14. f5 Bh5
$19) 13... Qe7 {Preparing a sacrifice on e5.} 14. Qe2 (14. f5 $2 Qxe5) (14. Na4
$5 Nxe5 $1 15. Bf2 (15. Nxc5 Ng4 16. Re1 Nxe3 17. Nxa6 Qf6 $15) (15. fxe5 Qxe5
$19) 15... Nxd3 16. f5 (16. Nxc5 Naxc5 17. f5 Nxb2 18. Qc2 Nbd3 19. fxg6 hxg6
20. Nb3 Nxb3 21. Qxb3 Nxf2 22. Rxf2 Rad8 $11) 16... Nxf2 17. Rxf2 Bxd4 18. Qxd4
Bh5 19. g4 Qh4 20. Rf4 g5 21. Qf6 Bxg4 22. h3 h5 23. Qh6 (23. hxg4 hxg4 $15 {
Black has four pawns for the piece and attacking chances.}) 23... f6 24. Qg6+
$11) 14... Nb4 15. Rad1 Nxe5 16. fxe5 (16. Nb3 d4 17. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 18. Nxd4 Rad8
19. Nb3 Bxd3 20. Qxe5 Qxe5 21. fxe5 Bxf1 22. Rxd8 Rxd8 23. Bxf1 Nd5 (23... Re8
24. Na5 Rxe5 25. Nxb7 Nd5 $13) 24. Ne4 Re8 25. Nd6 Rxe5 26. Nxb7 Re1 $13) (16.
a3 Bxd3 17. Rxd3 Nexd3 18. axb4 Nxb4 $17 {Rapport,J (2308)-Velikic,A (2278)
Vrnjacka Banja 2020 (0-1, 54)}) 16... Qxe5 17. Nf5 Bxe3+ 18. Qxe3 Qxe3+ 19.
Nxe3 d4 20. Rf4 Rfd8 (20... c5 21. Ned5) (20... Rad8 21. Ne2 Rfe8 22. Be4 Bxe4
$2 23. Rxe4 Rxe4 24. dxe4 $18) 21. Ne2 (21. Nb1 Nxd3 $19) 21... Re8 (21... Nxd3
22. Rxd4 $1) 22. Rxd4 Rxe3 23. Rxb4 Rxe2 24. Rxb7 Rc2 $11 *

