Bxd4 Qxd4 22. Qxd4 Rxd4 23. Rfe1 Bxe5 24. Rxe5 b6 $17 {Black is better as d3
is a huge weakness} 25. Be4 Rc8 26. Bxh7+ Kxh7 27. Re4 Rd5 28. Ra4 Rc7 29. Kg2
Kg6 30. Rd2 Rcd7 31. f4 Kf6 32. d4 g5 33. fxg5+ hxg5 34. Kf3 Kg6 35. Rc4 f6 (
35... b5) 36. a4 R5d6 37. Ke3 f5 38. Rcc2 Rh7 39. Rh2 Rh4 40. Rcg2 Kf6 41. Rf2
Kg6 42. Rfg2 a5 43. Rh1 Rh8 44. Rhh2 Rc6 45. Kd3 Rhc8 46. Rc2 Rxc2 47. Rxc2
Rxc2 48. Kxc2 Kf6 49. Kd3 Ke7 50. Ke3 Kd6 51. Kf2 fxg4 52. hxg4 Kd5 53. Ke3 e5
{The pawn endgame is trivially winning for Black so Radjabov chose to resign}
0-1

