Nf3 h6 7. O-O Bh7 8. d3 Be7 (8... Nbd7 {Once again, keep in mind that rushing
with Nbd7 might lead to an unpleasant position if White pushes e4} 9. Nbd2 Bd6
10. cxd5 exd5 (10... cxd5 11. e4 dxe4 12. dxe4 Be7 13. Nd4 O-O 14. Qe2 $16 {
[%csl Rd8][%cal Rf1d1,Rd1d8]}) 11. e4 $16 {[%csl Re8]}) 9. Nbd2 O-O 10. a3 a5
11. Ra2 Nbd7 12. Qa1 Bd6 13. e4 (13. Ne5 Nxe5 (13... Re8 {sets up a creative
trap} 14. Nxd7 (14. Rc1 Bf8 {[%cal Rd7e5,Rf6d7]}) 14... Nxd7 15. Bxg7 $6 e5 16.
